      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems with analytical solutions were used to verify each solver. Patch tests and manufactured-solution checks confirm correct implementation of the linear-elastic constitutive routines used in this analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence studies were performed on the pedicle screw and rod geometry. Peak von Mises stress and construct stiffness changed by less than 2% between the medium and fine meshes, confirming discretization error is within acceptable bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Direct sparse solver with double-precision arithmetic used throughout. Residual norms monitored and confirmed below 1e-8 for all load steps. No iterative convergence issues observed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Independent review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments performed by a second analyst at each participating organization. Discrepancies resolved prior to result submission."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Linear-elastic continuum mechanics with frictional contact at screw-rod interface. Model form is well-established for metallic implant stiffness prediction under static loading; literature precedent supports applicability to this construct geometry."
    },
